No follow-up attempts are possible. No further information is expected.   Additional information: This past Friday afternoon and received booster shot for COVID vaccine. Within less than 24 hours he started to experience diarrheal discharge of both goop and intestinal matter. It continued for about a day and a half maybe two. One was to drink Gatorade and he did that and to eat bland stuff. The diarrhea, at least temporarily was discontinuing. The doctors office said to take a container with the stuff to the local clinic in (withheld). He did that this morning. They were not interested and sent him to get COVID tested and he did that. Now they tell him that he would be informed after a couple of days. He was not scheduled for an appointment with a physician today. He did not know if this is over yet. It was not very pleasant. He tried to call VAERS and the only thing they were good for sending him a form to fill out. Caller has no indication it has been reported including at the clinic. He talked with a nurse and got COVID test. It has tapered off after he drank Gatorade and did not eat very much. He has only had a couple of ripe bananas and toast over 24 hour period. And Gatorade that has no sugar. He took a couple Ricola candies and those went down ok. Prior to that he was drinking water and had cut down on medication and practically everything else. Finally he stopped passing whatever. Initially it was coming out like chocolatey goop. Then the very last one occurred last night. After most of it had dissipated, it was a couple of farts and couple of blood drops. He did not notice blood in prior discharges. It got all over everything. Once it was going to come it was going to come. It was not pleasant. From what has been said to him continuing and disabling diarrhea was not associated with booster shot yet. That was what he has heard. Loss of fluid has been pointed out to him several times as a dangerous situation. It has tapered off after he drank Gatorade and did not eat very much.   Description of complaint: Caller reporting adverse event with booster shot for COVID vaccine. The reason he got it was because the first and second shot seemed to be very settling for him. With limited medical background, his impression is either the first or second may have settled and activated the immune system with the other viral complications which were documented over the years. That is a wild guess. He w  as very surprised there was a reaction to this. It could be an over reaction of immune system. They sent him to get COVID nasal test. In 2 days he will get the results. If for some reason he has acquired disimmunity there will be more questions.    No follow-up attempts are possible. No further information is expected.

The other symptom she noticed which was a little unusual was she woke up this morning and noticed her gums in her mouth were swollen and tender to the touch. It is a little unusual, but she knows there are glands under the jaw which could explain it, she could have a potential autoimmune reaction. The complaint for lack of effect of the Pfizer Biontech Covid-19 Vaccine Injectable lot EW0178 was investigated. The investigation included reviewing manufacturing and packaging batch records, deviation investigations, analytical release test results, and an analysis of complaint history for the reported lot. The final scope was determined to be the reported finished EW0178, fill lot EP8729, and the bulk formulated drug product EP8610. A complaint sample was not returned. No related quality issues were identified during the investigation. There is no impact on product quality. No root cause or CAPA were identified as the complaint was not confirmed. All release testing performed prior to the release of the reported batch was within specifications.   The lot number for bnt162b2 (dose 1) was not provided and will be requested during follow up.

The patient's past medical history, medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided. In December 2021, the patient received a dose  dose of suspect INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE, formulation, strength, dose and lot number not reported via unknown route in unknown administration site for immunisation. In DEC-2021 the patient developed a non-serious event "excruciating pain in arm" (pain in extremity) (unknown latency) following the administration of INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE. In DEC-2021 the patient developed a non-serious event "muscle aches; debilitating aches in her legs and buttocks" (myalgia) (unknown latency) following the administration of INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE. In DEC-2021 the patient developed a non-serious event "headache" (unknown latency) following the administration of INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE. It was reported that "Patient had excruciating pain in her arm, but not the arm the vaccine was administered in. Pain went away after 15 minutes. Compared pain to heart attack. - Muscle aches that are not normal muscle aches. Caller stated they were debilitating aches in her legs and buttocks for about four days. - Headache; caller stated she does not usually have headaches". Action taken with QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT INFLUENZA VACCINE (FLUBLOK QIV) was not applicable for all the events. It was not reported if the patient received a corrective treatment for the events (excruciating pain in arm, muscle aches; debilitating aches in her legs and buttocks, headache). At time of reporting, the outcome was Recovered / Resolved in December 2021 for the events (excruciating pain in arm, muscle aches; debilitating aches in her legs and buttocks) and was Unknown for the event (headache).

Passed out/fainted; The patient received Flucelvax Quadrivalent and Spikevax on the same day, both in left deltoid; This spontaneous case was received on 22-Dec-2021 from a pharmacist (reference number: SEQW21-06337) and concerned a 29-year-old, male patient.  The patient's concurrent condition included hypoglycaemia before injections (the patient had not eaten all day before receiving both vaccines). The was not taking any concomitant medications.   On 22-Dec-2021, the patient was vaccinated with Flucelvax Quadrivalent (influenza vaccine, subunit influenza virus vaccine polyvalent; dose: 0.5 ml, route of administration: intramuscular and anatomical location: left deltoid) for influenza prophylaxis The batch number reported was 309621 and expiry date 30-Jun-2022.  On the same day, the patient was vaccinated with a non-company, co-suspect Spikevax (elasomeran; route of administration: intramuscular, anatomical location: left deltoid, dose and indication: not reported) (explicitly coded as 'Product administration error'). The batch number was not reported.  On the same day, shortly after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent and Spikevax, the patient fainted/passed out for less than a minute. Pharmacist called for an ambulance and provided a Coke for the patient to drink in the meantime. Pharmacist stated that patient felt fine after drinking the Coke and walked out with the paramedics.  On the same day, the patient recovered from the event.  The reporter did not provide a causality assessment.  The event of 'faint' was considered to be medically significant by a Physician within Seqirus's Pharmacovigilance and Risk Management Department.  Company comment: On the same day, shortly after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent and Spikevax, the patient fainted for less than a minute. Causality is assessed as possibly related, although confounded by co-suspect. The patient received Flucelvax Quadrivalent and Spikevax on the same day, both in left deltoid. Product administration error is assessed as unrelated per company's conventions.; Sender's Comments: On the same day, shortly after receiving Flucelvax Quadrivalent and Spikevax, the patient fainted for less than a minute. This was not a new condition to me (hence the AICD) but it was the first time being shocked in over 2.5 years, and I have not been shocked since then. The labs run that day show no electrolyte imbalance nor any other common cause that might explain why I was shocked.  I know the Janssen vaccine may cause myocarditis, a common symptom of which is cardiac arrhythmias. I did ask my electrophysiology cardiologist before my vaccination if it was safe for me to do so, and he agreed the risk was worth it. I did not think at the time I was shocked that it might be vaccine-related. I have since asked my EP cardiologist several times if there was any data gathered that might answer the question of whether or not I had myocarditis on June 11, 2021. No one will answer that question.
LAB_DATA: The following labs were drawn and measured: CBC, comprehensive metabolic panel, TSH, and magnesium
OTHER_MEDS: Flecainide, metoprolol, cabergoline, cetirizne, Vitamin D3, Vitamin C

Patient stablized well with down trending troponins and inflammatory markers Hemoglobin stable able to eat and drink Discharged home on protonix and carafate on 12/30/21 Ultimately diagnosed with EBV and hyperinflammatory state. No Misc given self resolving fever and downtrending inflammation without treatement. No myocarditis given normal echo, ekgs, and normal cardiac MRI. It was felt that the elevated troponins were due to cross reactivity with EBV.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hand reaction beginning 8 days after booster shot. Began with hand itchiness and pain Friday evening of December 17, continued Saturday, December 18 with wheal hives in back, shoulder, arms area, with swelling and pain on arms. Unable to make a fist and pain in torso. By Sunday, December 19, more hives in naval and crotch area appeared, with more pain in entire torso and difficulty moving / getting up and out of bed, continued swelling in arms and wheals appearance all over body, and palpitations. Had to go to ER department for treatment with Benadryl, Dexamethasone and Pepcid. Discharged and took prednisone prescribed dosage on Monday, December 20, and by early morning of Tuesday, December 21st, continued with the swelling, pain, muscle aches, shaking, palpitations and heat emanating from body, and tight throat with extreme difficulty swallowing. Then returned to ER for another treatment, and was given muscle relaxant and discharged. By afternoon of the same day, Tuesday, December 21st, extreme swelling all over body appeared, and reached anaphylaxis, and had to call emergency.  Was administered dexamethasone, epinephrine and benadryl by paramedics and taken to Hospital ER. Was then admitted for 2 nights of observation and received high doses of dexamethasone steroid and benadryl to treat edema caused by anaphylaxis. Experiencing dizziness,  headaches, sweaty hands and feet,  muscle aches, with heat emanating from body, with itchiness. Chest tightness with breathing difficulty. Discharged with a taper of dexamethasone prescription, benadryl as needed, and zyrtec daily. Still experiencing all symptoms on and off in variating degrees, but more extreme at night.
LAB_DATA: Covid Tests plus blood work on every ER visit. 12/19, 12/20, 12/21. Strep Throat test 12/21. EKG 12/21. Echocardiogram 12/22. EKG 12/30.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patients came in with her parents to get her pfizer shot for covid-19.  The shot was administered by RPh into the left deltoid with a 5/8 inch needle for a dose of 0. 2 ml of NDC. The dose was given at 2:35 PM and within 5 minutes, pts mother got the pharmacist's attention to say that she was not feeling well. This occurred immediately after the father, got his moderna shot. The child indicated that there was something in her throat and that she had trouble breathing. Pt looked pale but her airway was unobstructed the entire time. She was given two doses of ammonia inhalant to keep her from fainting. I counseled the parents on the possible need for an epipen in the event that she starts have physical signs of hypoxia or an obstructed airway. No epipen was given since there was not airway obstruction or signs of hypoxia. The parents ask if we could give her some water but I advised against it due to choking risk. No hives we observed. Paramedics arrived at about 2:50 PM and did an assessment, which her Oxygen levels were above 98 and indicated that they were within normal limits and confirmed that no hives were present. The patient remained alert and orientated the entire time and was speaking normally. The mom did indicate that the child had a heart murmur after the child started to have symptoms post vaccination; however, this was not indicated on the PCQF. The parents called after patient was taken to the hospital to ask about how much vaccine was given (the dose) and asked us to email them the copy. I sent the copy to them as requested and also pointed out that the information was also on the white covid vaccination card that we gave them along with the sheet for Pfizer.
HISTORY: Heart Murmur- was not indicated on questionnaire- was disclosed after vaccination

SYMPTOM_TEXT: at 9:00 AM on 11/7/2021 (14.5 days after my Moderna COVID-19 booster), I noticed my neck was itching and saw a significant sized rash on the right side of my neck. I subsequently noticed hives covering my entire lower abdomen and part of my lower back. I took a Benadryl 25mg pill and the rash/hives subsided within the hour. Later that evening, the rash and hives were back on my neck, back, and stomach and had spread to my shoulders and legs. I saw my allergist (whom I see not for allergies, but for asthma) the next day and they had me start taking Zyrtec.   The hives and rashes progressively got worse throughout the week to the point that my husband had to call EMS to our home on 11/26/21 when the hives had spread to my face and I experienced tongue swelling and throat closing (anaphylactic symptoms). My allergist started me on a 5 day prednisone course the next night as well as Allegra 180mg in the morning and at night with a Zyrtec mid-day. the prednisone helped mitigate (not completely but mostly) the hives for approximately 7 days (5 days on the medication and then 48 hours afterward), but they promptly came back after completion of the steroids.  My period was also 12 days late during the onset of this issue, which is never is. It now appears to be back on track a month later.
LAB_DATA: During this time, my allergist had me do a litany of blood tests including: peanut, soybean, milk, eggs, corn, tree nuts, seafood, shellfish, chocolate, coconut, sunflowers, and chickpeas (all of which were negative) to rule out allergies. My thyroid was also checked and proved to be normal. Several autoimmune markers were checked (including those for Lupus and RA), with all being negative. I took a COVID test and was negative. I also am not pregnant. My allergist also checked my number of COVID antibodies from the vaccine and that number proved to be higher than what the lab can test for (>2500) and believes that the Moderna booster shot is causing an inappropriate immune response resulting in chronic dermatographia, hives, and rash all over my body. I have never had hives before and am otherwise completely healthy. I am almost 6 weeks into this, on 7 antihistamine pills per day, and yet this still is not completely under control.
OTHER_MEDS: spironolactone 100mg 1x per day; Flovent inhaled steroid for asthma, 2 puffs 2x per day
